verbose_text: The mode of multivariate analysis showed that diabetes (beta = 3.594; P = 0.040), hepatitis C infection (beta = 4.057; P = 0.008), levels of serum albumin (beta = -5.656; P = 0.024), C-peptide (beta = -0.292; P = 0.002), ABI (beta = -9.041; P = 0.031), and Ln transformed hsCRP were significantly associated with BDI as shown in Table XREF_TABLE.
